nnsec.client
Class CommModule

java.lang.Object
  nnsec.client.CommModule

public class CommModule
extends java.lang.Object

This class implements the related interface to turn himself into a remote class, so that users can export remote instances of CommModule.

createConnection

public void createConnection(java.lang.String host,
                             int port,
                             java.lang.String identifier)
                      throws CommModule.ConnectionException
This method permits to create connection with the server, then the client can retrieves an associated server part with which it can exploits the protocol.

Parameters:
host - server ip address.
port - server port.
identifier - server identifier (name used to bind the object in the rmi registry).
Throws:
CommModule.ConnectionException - thrown when some errors occur connecting with the server.

destroyConnection

public void destroyConnection()
This method destroies previously estabilished connection. In fact, it simply sets to null the server part remote reference.

isConnectionAvailable

public boolean isConnectionAvailable()
This method permits to control if a connection is available. In fact, it simply check if there is a valid server part remote reference.

Returns:
true if a connection is available, false otherwise.

getOutputs

public java.lang.String[] getOutputs(int netID,
                                     java.lang.String[] inputs)
                              throws CommModule.ConnectionException
This method permits to use a remote neural network showed by the server, submitting inputs and obtaining results. This is the client central method involved into the protocol.

Parameters:
netID - neural network identifier.
inputs - neural network inputs, in a specific syntax.
Returns:
neural network outputs, in a specific syntax.
Throws:
CommModule.ConnectionException - thrown as a consequence of RemoteException excesption.
